This paper is about learning communication strategies for multiple agents, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems. Therefore, cs.MA is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses deep reinforcement learning, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper proposes a gating mechanism to prune messages, which involves making decisions based on data, a topic covered in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with control policies for multiple agents, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
